  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some of the best books for IITJEE?",
  "response": "Preparing for the IIT JEE, one of the most challenging engineering entrance exams in India, requires a strategic approach and access to high-quality resources. Here are some of the best books recommended for IIT JEE preparation across the major subjects:\n\n### Mathematics\n1. **\"Objective Mathematics\" by R.D. Sharma** - Comprehensive coverage of concepts with numerous practice problems.\n2. **\"IIT Mathematics\" by M.L. Khanna** - Offers a variety of problems with detailed explanations, good for understanding complex concepts.\n3. **\"Higher Algebra\" by Hall and Knight** - Classic text for mastering algebraic concepts.\n4. **\"Problems in Calculus of One Variable\" by I.A. Maron** - Excellent for calculus practice.\n5. **\"Trigonometry\" by S.L. Loney** - Offers a clear understanding of trigonometry.\n\n### Physics\n1. **\"Concepts of Physics\" (Vol. 1 and 2) by H.C. Verma** - Essential for understanding fundamental concepts with solved problems.\n2. **\"Understanding Physics\" by D.C. Pandey** - A series covering mechanics, thermodynamics, and more, packed with problems for practice.\n3. **\"Problems in General Physics\" by I.E. Irodov** - Great for advanced problem-solving practice.\n4. **\"Fundamentals of Physics\" by Halliday, Resnick, and Walker** - Comprehensive text covering a wide range of topics.\n\n### Chemistry\n#### Physical Chemistry\n1. **\"Physical Chemistry\" by O.P. Tandon** - Covers theory and applications extensively.\n2. **\"Physical Chemistry\" by P.W. Atkins** - Offers detailed insights and in-depth understanding.\n\n#### Organic Chemistry\n1. **\"Organic Chemistry\" by Morrison and Boyd** - Detailed exploration of organic reactions and mechanisms.\n2. **\"Organic Chemistry\" by O.P. Tandon** - Good for basic concepts and problem solving.\n\n#### Inorganic Chemistry\n1. **\"Concise Inorganic Chemistry\" by J.D. Lee** - Clear understanding of inorganic chemistry principles.\n2. **\"Inorganic Chemistry\" by O.P. Tandon** - Covers essential concepts with practice questions.\n\n### Additional Recommendations\n- **\"Problems in Physics\" by S.S. Krotov** - For students looking to challenge themselves with tough problems.\n- **Previous Years' IIT JEE Papers** - Practicing past papers is crucial to understand the pattern and difficulty level.\n\nIt's important to complement these books with consistent practice, mock tests, and coaching materials if accessible. Additionally, online resources and video tutorials can provide supplementary learning and clarify difficult topics. Regular practice and dedication are key to excelling in the IIT JEE.",
